TIME SERIES FORECASTING - ROSE WINE DATASET¶

Problem Statement:¶

For this particular assignment, the data of different types of wine sales in the 20th century is to be analysed. Both of these data are from the same company but of different wines. As an analyst in the ABC Estate Wines, you are tasked to analyse and forecast Wine Sales in the 20th century.

Now first we have to treat the missing observations in the dataset

We are using interpolation method to treat the missing observations. This interpolation method is to use a spline to connect the values. Using a spline interpolation requires you specify the order (number of terms in the polynomial). In our case, an order of 1 is just fine.

In [14]:

Building Triple Exponential Smoothing model or Holt-Winter's model:¶

Since our data shows trend and seasonality patterns, it will good to use Triple Exponential smoothing model for this data.

In [56]:
#importing ExponentialSmoothing, SimpleExpSmoothing and Holt

from statsmodels.tsa.api import ExponentialSmoothing, SimpleExpSmoothing, Holt

#copying the train and test set

TES_train = train.copy()
TES_test = test.copy()

#creating class

TES_model = ExponentialSmoothing(TES_train['Rose'],trend='additive',seasonal='multiplicative',freq='M')

# Fitting the Simple Exponential Smoothing model and asking python to choose the optimal parameters
TES_model_autofit = TES_model.fit(optimized=True)

for i in np.arange(0.3,1.1,0.1):
    for j in np.arange(0.3,1.1,0.1):
        for k in np.arange(0.3,1.1,0.1):

            TES_train['predict',i,j,k] = TES_model_alpha_i_j_k.fittedvalues
            TES_test['predict',i,j,k] = TES_model_alpha_i_j_k.forecast(steps=55)
        
            RMSE_TES_train_new = metrics.mean_squared_error(TES_train['Rose'],TES_train['predict',i,j,k],squared=False)
            
            RMSE_TES_test_new = metrics.mean_squared_error(TES_test['Rose'],TES_test['predict',i,j,k],squared=False)
            
            resultsDf_new = resultsDf_new.append({'Alpha Values':i,'Beta Values':j,'Gamma Values':k,
                                                  'Train RMSE':RMSE_TES_train_new,'Test RMSE':RMSE_TES_test_new}
                                                 , ignore_index=True)

Taking Alternative Hypothesis $H_1$- Series is Stationary

#creating a function to test the stationarity of the time series


def Stationarity_test(timeseries):
    
    #rolling mean
    rolmean = timeseries.rolling(window=7).mean() 
    #rolling standard deviation
    rolstd = timeseries.rolling(window=7).std()   

    #Plotting
    
    original = plt.plot(timeseries, color='pink',label='Original')
    mean = plt.plot(rolmean, color='black', label='Rolling mean')
    std = plt.plot(rolstd, color='green', label = 'Rolling std')
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.title('Rolling Mean & Standard Deviation')
    plt.show(block=False)

10.Comment on the model thus built and report your findings and suggest the measures that the company should be taking for future sales.¶

Some Measures that company need to take care of in future:¶

We have observed the sales pattern of rose wine from the year 1980 till 1995 and found out that few points that need to understand:

Fall in trend is clearly visible from yearly plot.

The maximum number of sales happened in the month of December due to some festive season and also because of the year end celebration, so we need to take care of all the arrangements for the customers by keep our stocks full at all point of sales center/shop.

We also need to take care of quality, the purity of material used to make the rose wine. This will definitely lead to advancement in sales

The lowest number of sales observed in the month of June.

We have build all the applicable models with our data and calculated RMSE values on all the test data.

After calculating RMSE, we got to know the Triple Exponential model is best for our data due to it's lowest RMSE value.

We have also predicted the sales for upcoming 12 months with confidence interval.

Trend was affecting too much and not up to the mark as expected. So we also need to take care of the better quality of the wine to get the attention and attraction of the customers.

If we are able to take these above steps carefully then definitely our sales of the Rose wine would be more in upcoming future.
